               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers (fols. 2ra, l.1 – 13ra, l.13)
 II)Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse "Ordinary of the Mass" (fols. 13ra, l.14 – 28vb, l.17)
 III)
                     Anaphoras (fols. 28vb – 78vb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 28vb.
                     l.18 – 36va, l.9)
 III-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 36va,
                     l.9 – 40ra, l.14)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa
                     (fols. 40ra, l.14 – 49ra, l.22)
 III-4) Anaphora of St Dioscorus (fols.
                     49rb, l.1 – 51va, l.13)
 III-5) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols. 51va,
                     l.13 – 56va, l.13)
 III-6) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 56va, l.14
                     – 61va, l.19)
 III-7) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols.
                     61va, l.20 – 68vb, l.7)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Athanasius (fols. 68vb, l.8
                     – 78vb, l.18).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
